ASSEMBLY SOLAR III, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Assembly Solar III, LLC ("Assembly Solar III") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Assembly Solar III generating facility ("Assembly Solar III Facility").
The Assembly Solar III Facility is a solar generating facility located in Shiawassee County, Michigan. The Assembly Solar III Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Michigan Electric Transmission Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Assembly Solar II's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Assembly Solar III Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Assembly Solar III's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Assembly Solar III shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $398,160.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $33,180.00.
